variant title: EXO x NATURE REPUBLIC Moisture Special Collection
cancel reason comments: I very much loved the first three-box I received. But couldn't enjoy the last one so much. Personally, I feel like there is a focus on collagen products but if including skincare I would like to see more moisturizing & hydrating stuff rather than collagen. Make-up products are a nice touch yes but risky since people might find the colors too bright for their complexions. I am pretty light-skinned yet I found them pretty light (the lip tints and the lipsticks in the 3rd and 4th box). Snacks are definitely awesome but rather than typical peach-flavored iced tea I would've loved to see something more interesting since Korea is a place where many interesting flavors exist at a wide range such as melon or banana-flavored things. Anyhow, I would love to come back for another subscription but for now, imma stick to shopping from your site individually. Thank you so much for your hard work! :)

cancel reason comments: Overall, I was disappointed in the merchandise that was in the boxes. The items were okay, but there were too many that simply didn't interest me to continue my annual subscription. Even though I haven't received the final box yet, I can't imagine it will change my mind about canceling. The lack of honest communication during the difficulties with shipping were quite unfortunate. You show these fabulous boxes on Instagram, filled with products that I would love, but often the items pictured are not included. The constant solicitations to join Facebook to be a part of the "Daebak Family" seems rather juvenile in my opinion. Lastly, most of the offers you send out for various sales, and the add-on items, if you have a subscription, are sold out almost instantly. I just can't think of a good reason to keep receiving the boxes, even though I love all things Korean, and had really high hopes for the Daebak Box in the beginning.
